statement:
Let $G$ be a finitely generated abelian group. Then there is a unique
expression of the form: $$G\cong
{\mathbb{Z}}^{r}\oplus{\mathbb{Z}}/n_1{\mathbb{Z}}\oplus{\mathbb{Z}}/n_2{\mathbb{Z}}\oplus\ldots\oplus{\mathbb{Z}}/n_s{\mathbb{Z}}$$
for some integers $r,n_i$ satisfying:
$$r\geq 0;\quad \forall i, n_i\geq 2;\quad n_{i+1}\mid n_i\ \text{for }
1\leq i\leq s-1.$$
